{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs72 The Book of Ezekiel

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 1}In the thirtieth year, in the fifth day of the fourth month, as I was among the captives by the River Chebar, the heavens were opened and I saw visions of God,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}{ }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and the hand of Jehovah was on me there.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And I looked and behold, a storm wind came from the north, a mighty cloud, surrounded by brightness and shot through with fire, and out of its midst gleamed something like shining\uc1\u8217* metal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And out of its midst appeared the forms of four living creatures. And this was their appearance: they had the form of a man,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}each had four faces and four wings;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}their legs were straighth and the soles of their feet were like the sole of a calf\uc1\u8217*s foot. They shone like polished bronze.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And the hands of a man were under their wings, on the four sides, and the wings of the four{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}touched each other, and their faces did not turn as they went; each went straight forward.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And this was the form of their faces: all four had in front the face of a man; on the right, the face of a lion; on the left the face of a bull; and behind, the face of an eagle.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Their wings were separated above, the one from the other; each wing of the pair was joined to its neighbor, while one pair of wings covered the upper part of the body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Each went straight forward; whither the spirit impelled him to go, he went, and they turned not as tLey went.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And in the midst of the living creatures was an appearance like glowing coals of fire, like torches, and it was moving up and down among the living creatures, and the fire was gleaming, and from the fire went forth lightning.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And as the living creatures moved to and fro, there was an appearance like lightning.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And I beheld the living creatures, and lo, a wheel was on the ground beside each of the four living creatures.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}The appearancer of the wheels was like topaz, - the four had the same form and their construction was as though one wheel were within another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}They went in whatever direction their four sides faced, and they did not turn as they went.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And their felloes - they were high and dreadful - were full of eyes, on all sides.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}And when the living creatures moved, the wheels moved beside them; and when the living creatures rose up from the earth, the wheels rose up;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}whithersoever spirit impelled them to go they went; and the wheels rose up beside them, for the spirit of the creatures was in the wheels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}When those moved, these moved, and when those stood still, these stood still, and when those rose up from the earth, the wheels rose up beside them, for the spirit of the creatures was in the wheels.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And on the heads of the creatures was a firmament, in appearance like crystal, stretched out above their heads.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Under the firmament their wings were stretched out straight, each touching the other, and two covering their upper body.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And I heard the sounds of the wings as the sound of many waters, like the voice of the Almighty, the sound of a tumult, like the sound of a multitude; and when they stood still, they folded their wings.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Above the firmament, which was over their heads, was something that resembled sapphire, in the form of a throne, and on the form of the throne was a form which resembled a man.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And I saw something like shining metal, which resembled fire, surrounded by brightness. From what seemed his loins, above and below, I saw what looked like fire, surrounded by brightness,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}like the bow which appears in a cloud, on a rainy day; such was the brightness round about. It was the appearance of the likeness of the glory of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
 And when I saw, I fell upon my face, and I heard the voice of one speaking.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Prophet\uc1\u8217*s Commission

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 2}Then Jehovah said to me, Son of man stand up on thy feet that I may speak with thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And the spirit entered into me, as he spoke to me, and made me stand upon my feet; and I heard him who spoke to me.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And he said to me, Son of man, I am about to send thee to the rebellious house of Israel; who have rebelled against me, both they and their fathers, even to this day.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}It is I who send thee to them that thou shouldst say to them: \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Whether they will hear or refuse to hear - for they are a rebellious house - they shall learn that a prophet is among them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And thou son of man, fear them not nor be dismayed at their words, though briars and thorns are about thee and thou dwellest among scorpions. Be not afraid of their words nor be dismayed at their looks; for they are a rebellious house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}But do thou speak my words to them, whether they hear or refuse to hear; for they are a rebellious house.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But thou son of man, hear what I say to thee. Be not rebellious like this rebellious house. Open thy mouth and eat what I give thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then I looked and there was stretched out to me a hand in which there was a roll of a book.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And he unrolled it before me and it was written within and without; and in it were written lamentations and mourning and woe.{\cf1\f1\fs22 3}And he said to me, Son of man, eat this roll and go speak to the house of Israel,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}2o I opened my mouth and he made me eat the roll.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And he said to me, Son of man, eat and be filled withm this roll which I give thee. Then I ate it and it was as sweet as honey in my mouth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And he said to me, Son of man, up, go to the house of Israel and speak my words to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}For thou art not sent to a people of strange speech, nor to many peoples whose words thou couldst not understand. Verily, if I sent thee to them, they would hear thee!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But the house of Israel will not be willing to hear thee, for they are not willing to hear me; for all the house of larael are bold and unyielding.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Behold I make thee as bold and unyielding as they.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}As adamant, harder than flint, have I made thy face. Be not afraid of them neither be dismayed at them. For they are a rebellious house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}He also said to me, Son of man, all of my words that I shall speak to thee receive in thy mind and hear with thine ears,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and go to the captives, the people of thy race, and speak to them and say to them: \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah\uc1\u8217* whether they hear or refuse to heed.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Ezekiel\uc1\u8217*s Appointment as a Watchman

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Then the spirit lifted me up and I heard behind me the sound of great rustling, as the Glory of Jehovah rose from its place; and{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}the sound of the wings of the living creatures touching one another, and the sound of the wheels beside them, even the sound of a great rustling.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}So the spirit lifted me up and took me away and I went in great excitement, for the hand of Jehovah was strong upon me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then I came to the captives at Tel-abib who dwelt by the canal Chebar, and I sat there overwhelmed among them seven days.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}At the end of seven days this word of Jehovah came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Son of man, I make thee a watchman to the house of Israel. When thou hearest a word from my mouth, thou shalt warn them from me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}When I say to the wicked, \uc1\u8217*Thou shalt surely die,\uc1\u8217* then if thou speak not to the wicked to warn him from his wicked way, so as to save his life, that wicked man shall die in his iniquity; but his blood will I require at thy hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But if thou warn a wicked man and he turn not from his wickedness nor from his wicked way, he shall die in his iniquity. But thou hast saved thyself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Again, when a righteous man turns from his righteousness and does wrong, and I lay a stumblingblock before him, he shall die; because thou hast not given him warning he shall die in his sin, for the righteous deeds which he hath done shall not be remembered; but his blood will I require at thy hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}But if thou warn the righteous man not to sin and he doth not sin, the righteous man shall surely live, because he took warning; and thou hast saved thyself.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Prophet\uc1\u8217*s Period of Silence

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And the hand of Jehovah was upon me and he said to me, Arise, go forth into the valley and there I will speak with thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Then I arose and went forth into the valley; and lo, there the Glory of Jehovah was standing, like the Glory that I saw by the River Cbebar. And I fell on my face.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And the spirit entered me and set me on my feet. And be spoke with me and said to me, Enter in, shut thyself up within thy house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And as for thee, O son of man, 1e will put bonds on thee and bind thee therewith, and thou shalt not go forth among them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And I wilql cause thy tongue to cleave to the roof of thy mouth, and thou shall be dumb, and thou shalt not be a reprover to them, for they are a rebellious house.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}But when I speak with thee, I will open thy mouth and thou shalt say to them: \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah.\uc1\u8217* Let him hear and let him forbear to hear who will, for they are a rebellious house.  
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Symbolic Representations of the Fate Awaiting Jerusalem

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 4}Do thou also, son of man, take a tile, and set it before thee, and portray upon it a city, even Jerusalem;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and lay siege against it, and build a siege wall against it, and throw up a mound against it; pitch camps also against it, and plant battering rams about it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And take thou an iron plate, and set it for a wall of iron between thee and the city: and set thy face toward it and so it shall be in a state of siege, and thou shalt lay a siege against it; and this is a sign to the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And do thou lie upon thy left side, and bear the iniquity of the house of Israel. According to the number of days thou liest on it thou shalt bear their iniquities.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}I assign thee for the years of their iniquity a fixed number of days, one hundred and ninety days. Thus thou shalt bear the iniquity of the house of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And when thou hast completed these, thou shalt lie on thy right side, and bear the guilt of the house of Judah forty days, a day for a year I assign thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And thou shalt turn thy face and thy bared arm toward the siege of Jerusalem, and prophesy against her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}See, I put bands upon thee, and thou shalt not turn from one side to the other until thou hast finished the days of thy siege.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Do thou also take for thyself wheat and barley, and beans and lentils, and millet and spelt, and put them in a vessel, and make bread for thyself of them. Thou shalt eat of it the number of the days that thou liest on thy side (one hundred and ninety days).{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Thou shalt eat thy food by weight, twenty shekels a day; at fixed intervals shalt thou eat it. Thou shalt eat it in the form of barley cakes, and bake it in their presence on human dung.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Thou shalt drink water by measure, one sixth of a bin; thou shalt drink it at fixed intervals.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}{ }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And Jehovah said, Thus shall the Israelites eat their food unclean among the nations, whither I shall drive them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And I said, Ah, Lord Jehovah, from my youth until now I have never been defiled, nor have I eaten what died of itself, or was torn by beasts, nor hath abominable flesh entered my mouth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Then he said to me, See, I allow thee to use cow\uc1\u8217*s dung instead of human dung: on it thou mayest prepare thy food.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}He also said to me, Son of man, I am about to break the staff of bread in Jerusalem; they shall eat bread by weight and in terror, and drink water by measure and in dismay,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}that, lacking bread and water, each man may be filled with dismay and waste away because of his iniquity.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 5 }And do thou, son of man, take a short sword and use it as a barber\uc1\u8217*s razor, and pass it over thy head and beard. Then take the balances and divide the hair.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}A third part burn in the fire in the midst of the city, when the days of the siege are complete; and take a third part and smite with the sword round about the city; and a third part scatter to the wind. But take a few of them and wrap them up in thy skirts;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}{ }{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and of these again take some and burn them in the fire.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Then thou shalt say to all the house of Israel, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah: "This is Jerusalem. I have set her in the midstu of the nations and countries round about her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But she hath rebelled against mine ordinances more wickedly than the nations; and against my statutes more than the countries round about her. For they rejected mine ordinances and have not walked in my statutes."{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore thus saith Jehovah: "Because ye have been more rebellious than the nations round about you, in that ye have not walked in my statutes nor kept my ordinances; but have done according to the ordinances of the nations that are round about you,"{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}therefore thus saith the Lord Jehovah,"behold I also am against thee and will execute judgment against thee in the sight of the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And I will do in thee that which I have not done and the like of which I will not do again, because of all thine abominations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Therefore fathers shall eat their sons in the midst of thee, and the sons shall eat their fathers. And I will execute judgment on thee, and I will scatter the whole remnant of thee to every wind.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Therefore, as I live," is the oracle of Jehovah, "because thou hast defiled my sanctuary with all my detestable things and with all thine abominations, I will also drive thee away. And mine eye shall not spare and I also will defile thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}A third part of these shall die by the pestilence and perish with famine in the midst of thee, and a third part shall fall by the sword round about thee, and a third part I will scatter to every wind and pursue with the sword.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Thus will mine anger be vented, and I will appease my fury on them, and they shall know that I, Jehovah, have spoken in mine indignation, when I have vented mine anger on them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And I will make thee a desolation among the nations which are about thee, in the eyes of every passer by.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And thou shalt be an object of scorn and derision, of instruction and dismay to the nations which are round about thee, when I execute judgments upon thee in anger and fury and in my wrathful rebukes, I, Jehovah, have promised.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}When I send against you mine evil arrows, which shall destroy you, I will send famine upon you and break your staff of life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And I will send upon you famine and evil beasts, and they shall bereave you, and pestilence and bloodshed shall pass through you, and I will bring a sword upon you; I, Jehovah, have said it."\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Judgment upon Guilty Judah

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 6 }This word of Jehovah also came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Son of man, set thy face against the mountains of Israel and prophesy against them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and say, \uc1\u8217*O mountains of Israel, hear the word of Jehovah: "Thus saith the Lord Jehovah to the mountains and the hills, to the ravines and the valleys: Behold, I am about to bring the sword against you and I will destroy your high places,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and your altars shall be shattered, and your sun pillars broken in pieces, and I will cause your slain to fall before your idols,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and I will scatter your bones about your altars.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}In all your dwelling places cities shall be laid waste, and the high places desolate, so that your altars shall be waste\uc1\u176* and desolate, and your idols shall be broken in pieces, and your sun pillars hewn down;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and the slain shall fall in your midst, and ye shall know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And when there shall be among the nations some of you who have escaped the sword, when ye are dispersed in the lands;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}then ye who have escaped will remember me among the nations whither ye are carried captive. I will crush the hearts of those who have adulterously turned from me, and the eyes which have adulterously turned after-their idols, and they shall loathe themselves for the wicked things which they have done, for all their abomination.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And they shall know that I, Jehovah, have not vainly said that would do them this evil."\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}This saith Jehovah, Clap thy hands and stamp thy feet and say, \uc1\u8217*Woe, woe, because of all the wicked abominations of the house of Israel, because with the sword, with famine, and with pestilence shall they fall.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}He who is far off shall die by pestilence, and he who is near shall fall by the sword, and he who is besieged shall die by famine: thus, I will vent my fury upon them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And they shall know that I am Jehovah, when their slain lie in the midst of their idols on every high hill, on every mountain top, and under every green tree, and under every leaf-clad terebinth, where they have offered sweet savior to all their idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And I will stretch out my hand against them to make the land waste and desolate from the wilderness to Riblah, in all their dwelling places; and they shall know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Nation\uc1\u8217*s Doom

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
\uc1\u8216*Moreover this word of Jehovah came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}O thou son of man, thus saith Jehovah to the land of Israel, \uc1\u8216*An end is come! Say, The end is come on the four quarters of the land!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Now is the end upon thee, and I will vent mine anger upon thee, and will judge thee according to thy deeds; and I requite thee for all thine abominations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And I will have no compassion on thee, neither will I pity; but I will requite thee for thy deeds, and thine abominations shall be in the midst of thee; and ye shall know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Thus saith Jehovah; Calamity follows calamity! Behold it cometh!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}An end is come; the end is come! it awaketh against thee! behold, it is come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}The doom is come upon thee, O inhabitant of the land! The time is come, the day is near, a day of tumult, and not of joyful shouting.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Now will I shortly pour out my wrath upon thee, and accomplish mine anger against thee, and will judge thee according to thy deeds; and I will requite thee all thine abominations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And I will not have compassion on thee, neither will I pity; I will bring upon thee according to thy ways; and thine abominations shall be in the midst of thee; and ye shall know that I, Jehovah, do smite.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}\uc1\u8220*Behold, the day! behold, it has come! thy doom hath gone forth; the sin hath blossomed, pride hath budded.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The support of the wicked shall be taken away without tumult or haste.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}The time is come, the day draweth near, let not the buyer rejoice, nor the seller mourn; for wrath is upon all her multitude.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}For the seller shall not return to that which is sold, nor will the buyer retain what this morning he bought.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}They have blown the trumpet, and have made all ready; but none goeth to the battle; for my wrath is upon all her pomp.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}The sword is without, and the pestilence and the famine within; he that is in the field shall die with the sword; and he that is in the city\uc1\u8212*famine shall devour him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}But those of them who escape shall escape, and shall be on the mountains like doves of the valleys, all of them moaning, each because of his iniquity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}All hands shall be feeble, and all knees shall be weak as water.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}They shall also gird them- selves with sackcloth, and horror shall cover them; and shame shall be upon all faces, and baldness upon all their heads.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}They shall cast their silver in the streets, and their gold shall be as an un- clean thing; their silver and their gold shall not be able to deliver them in the day of the wrath of Jehovah; they shall not satisfy their appetite, neither fill their stomachs; because these have been the occasion of their iniquity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Its ornamental beauty they have made an object of pride, and from it they have made the images of their abominations and detestable things. Therefore I will make it to them as an unclean thing,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}and I will give it into the hands of strangers as a prey, and to the wicked of the earth for a spoil; and they shall profane it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}My face will I turn also from them, and they shall profane my jewel; and robbers shall enter into it, and profane it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Make a complete destruction, for the land is full of bloody crimes, and the city is full of violence.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Therefore I will bring the worst of the heathen nations, and they shall take possession of their houses; I will also make the pride of their strength to cease; and their holy places shall be profaned.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Anguish cometh; and they shall seek peace, and there shall be none.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Mischief shall come upon mischief, and rumor shall be upon rumor; and they shall seek a vision of the prophet; but the law shall perish from the priest, and counsel from the elders.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And the prince shall clothe himself with dismay, and the hands of the people of the land shall tremble; I will do to them after their way, and according to their deserts will I judge them; and they shall know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jerusalem\uc1\u8217*s Guilt and Punishment

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 8}1n the sixth year, on the fifth day of the sixth month, as I was sitting in my house, and the elders of Judah were sitting before me, the hand of Jehovah fell upon me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Then I beheld and there was a form like that of a man; from that which appeared to be his loins downward, fire; and from his loins upward, like something shining, as the gleam of glowing metal.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And he stretched forth the form of a hand, and took me by a lock of my hair: and the spirit lifted me up between earth and heaven, and brought me in the visions of God to Jerusalem, to the door of the entrance of the northern gateway of the inner court, where stood the image of jealousy, which provokes his jealousy.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And there was the glory of the God of Israel, like that which I saw in the plain.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
