{\cf1\f1\fs22 20}Now in the seventh year, on the tenth day of the fifth month, certain of the elders of Israel came to inquire of Jehovah, and sat before me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Then this word of Jehovah came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Son of man, speak to the elders of Israel, and say to them, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah: "Have ye come to consult me? As I live, saith Jehovah, I will not be consulted by you."\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Wilt thou judge them, son of man, wilt thou judge them? Cause them to know the abomination of their fathers;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}5 and say to them,\uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah: "In the day when I chose Israel, and swore to the descendants of the house of Jacob, and made myself known to them, in the land of Egypt, when I swore to them, saying, I am Jehovah, your God;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}in that day I swore to them, to bring them out of the land of Egypt into a land that I had given them, a land flowing with milk and honey, the glory of all lands.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And I said to them, Cast ye away every man the abominations of his eyes, and defile not yourselves with the idols of Egypt: I am Jehovah your God."\uc1\u8217*
