{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}So I caused them to go out of the land of Egypt, and brought them into the wilderness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}.And I gave them my statutes, and showed them mine ordinances, which if a man do he shall live thereby.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Moreover I gave them my sabbaths, to be a sign between me and them, that they might know that it is I, Jehovah, who sanctifieth them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}But the house of Israel rebelled against me in the wilderness: they walked not in my statutes, and they rejected mine ordinances, which if a man keep he shall live thereby; and my sabbaths they greatly profaned. Then I said I would pour out my wrath upon them in the \uc1\u183*wilderness to consume them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But I acted for my name\uc1\u8217*s sake, lest it should be profaned in the sight of the nations, in whose sight I brought them out.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Moreover I swore to them in the wilderness, that I would not bring them into the land which I had given them, a land flowing with milk and honey, the glory of all lands;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}because they had rejected mine ordinances, and walked not in my statutes, and profaned my sabbaths; for their heart went after their idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Nevertheless mine eye spared them, and I destroyed them not, neither did I completely destroy them in the wilderness.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And I said to the children in the wilderness, Walk ye not in the statutes of your fathers, nor observe their ordinances, nor defile yoursehes with their idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I am Jehovah your God; walk in my statutes, and keep mine ordinances, and do them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}and keep my sabbaths; and they shall be a sign between me and you, that ye may know that I am Jehovah your God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}But the children rebelled against me; they walked not in my statutes, neither kept mine ordinances to do them, which if a man do he shall live thereby; they profaned my sabbaths. Then I said I would pour out my wrath upon them, to accomplish mine anger against them in the wilderness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Nevertheless I withdrew my hand, and acted for my name\uc1\u8217*s sake, lest it should be profaned in the sight of the nations, in whose sight I brought them forth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Moreover I swore to them in the wilderness that I would scatter them among the nations, and disperse them through the countries,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}because they had not executed mine ordinances, but had rejected my statutes, and had profaned my sabbaths, and because their eyes were turned toward the idols of their fathers{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Moreover I gave them statutes that were not good, and ordinances wherein they should not live;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}and I defiled them by their own gifts, through causing all their first-born to pass through the fire, that I might make them desolate, so that they might know that I am Jehovah.
