{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And Oholah played the harlot, disloyal to me, and she lusted after her lovers, after the Assyrians, warriors,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}clad in purple, prefects, and governors, attractive youths \uc1\u8212* all of them, horsemen riding on horses;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and she bestowed her harlotries upon them \uc1\u8212* choice men of Assyria, all of them, and after them she lusted, with all their idols she defiled herself.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And she did not abandon her harlotries from the days when she was in Egypt; in her youth they have lain with her, and they have handled her virgin bosom, and lavished their harlotry upon her.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore I gave her up into the hands of her lovers, into the hands of the Assyrians, after whom she lusted.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}They uncovered her nakedness, they took her sons and her daughters, and her they slew with the sword, so that she became an example to women, and punishment was inflicted upon her.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Her sister, Oholibah, saw, yet she carried her lust and her adulteries beyond those of her sister;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}after the Assyrians she lusted, prefects, warriors, clad in purple, horsemen riding on horses, attractive youths, all of them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And I saw that she was defiling herself; they both followed the same way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}But she carried her harlotries further; and when she saw men pictured on walls, figures of Chaldeans, pictured in vermilion,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}their loins girded with sashes, their heads adorned with turbans, in appearance all of them like captains, portraits of Babylonians, whose native land was Chaldea,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}she lusted after them, as she looked upon them, and sent messengers to them into Chaldea.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then the Chaldeans went in to her, into the bed of love, and they defiled her with their harlotry, so that she was unclean because of them, and she loathed them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Thus she revealed her harlotries, and her nakedness was seen, and I loathed her, as I had loathed her sister.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But she increased her harlotries, remembering the days of her youth, when she committed harlotry in the land of Egypt,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}and she lusted after her paramours, whose lust was like that of asses and stallions.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}And thou soughtest the lewdness of thy youth, when? thy bosom was handled in Egypt, and thy youthful breasts were pressed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Therefore, Oholibah, Thus saith Jehovah, Behold I am about to stir up thy lovers against thee, those whom thou loathest, and I will bring them against thee on every side,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}Babylonians, all the Chaldeans, Pekod, and Shoa, and Koa all the Assyrians with them, attractive youths, prefects and governers, all of them, captains and warriors, all of them riding on horses.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}They shall come against thee with a multitude of chariots and wagons and with a host of peoples, with shields, buckler, and helmet, will they array themselves round about thee. And I will lay judgment before them, and by their sentence they shall condemn thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And I will pour out my jealous indignation upon thee, and they shall deal with thee in fury; they shall cut off thy nose and thine ears, and the rest of thee shall fall by the sword; they shall carry off thy sons and thy daughters, and the rest of thee shall be con- sumed with fire.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}They shall strip thee of thy garments, and take away thy beautiful jewels.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}So I will remove thy lewdness from thee, and thy harlotries from the land of Egypt, and thou shalt not lift up thine eyes to them nor remember Egypt any more.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}For thus saith Jehovah, Behold I am about to give thee into the hands of those whom thou hatest, into the hands of those whom thou loathest,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}and they shall deal with thee in hatred, and take away all the fruit of thy labor, and leave thee bare and naked, and the shame of thine adulteries shall be laid bare,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}for thy lewdness! and thy harlotries have done this to thee, in that thou hast played the harlot with the nations by defiling thyself* with their idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}In the way of thy sister hast thou gone, and I will give her cup into thy hands.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Thus saith Jehovah: 
\par}

{\pard
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Thy sister\uc1\u8217*s cup shalt thou drink, it is deep and large; 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Thou shalt be an object of scorn and derision! it holds much! 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 \uc1\u8220*Thou shalt be filled with drunkenness and affliction\uc1\u8212*a cup of terror and desolation! 
