{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 Also let the bones seethe within it.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}For thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*Woe to the bloody city, that caldron full of rust, from which the rust is not yet gone!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For her blood is still in her midst. On the naked rock she hath placed it; she hath not poured it out on the ground, that the dust might cover it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}To stir up fury, to execute vengeance, I have put her blood upon the naked rock, that it may not be covered.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore thus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8217*Woe to the bloody city! I myself will pile high the wood.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Heap up the wood, kindle the fire, cook the flesh, brew the broth. and let the bones be burned. Take out its pieces, piece by piece, for them no lot is cast.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Then let it stand empty upon the coals, that it may be heated, that its copper may glow, that the impurity within it may be melted out, its rust cleansed away;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}yet its great rust is not removed from it by fire!
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Its rust is thy impurity because of lewdness, because I have sought to cleanse thee and thou wouldst not become clean from thine uncleanness. Thou shalt be cleansed no more, until I satisfy my fury upon thee,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}I, Jehovah, have spoken. It comes, and I will do it! I will not turn back nor pity nor repent, according to thy ways and thy deeds will I judge thee,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}This word of Jehovah came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Son of man, behold, I am about to take from thee the desire of thine eyes in an instant, yet thou shalt not mourn nor weep nor shed tears.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Sigh in silence, mourn not for the dead, put on thy turban, thy sandals on thy feet, do not cover thy beard, nor eat the bread of mourning.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}So I spoke to the people in the morning and in the evening my wife died, and on the morrow I did as I was commanded,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}and the people said to me, Will you not tell us why you do so?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And I said to them, this word of Jehovah came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Say to the house of Israel, \uc1\u8220*Thus saith Jehovah: Behold, I am about to profane my sanctuary, the pride of your strength, the delight of your eyes, and the joy of your souls. And your sons and your daughters, whom you have left, shall fall by the sword.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Ye shall do as I have done, ye shall not cover your beard nor eat the bread of mourning;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}your turbans shall be upon your heads and your sandals upon your feet, ye shall not weep, but ye shall pine away because of your iniquities. And ye shall stare in confusion at one another.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Ezekiel shall be a sign to you, just as he does shall ye do when it comes. Then ye shall know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And thou, son of man, on the day that I take from them their strength, their proud joy, and delight of their eyes, the joy of their souls, their sons and their daughters,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}on that day shall one who has escaped come to thee to inform thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}On that day shall thy mouth be opened to the fugitive; and thou shalt speak and be no longer silent, and thou shalt be a sign to them that they may know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Judgment against Israel\uc1\u8217*s Malignant Foes

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 25}\uc1\u8216*This word of Jehovah came to me again, "{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Son of man, turn thy face toward the Ammonites, and prophesy against them,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and say to the Ammonites: \uc1\u8216*Hear the word of Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Thus saith Jehovah, Because thou saidst, Aha, over my sanctuary when it was defiled, and over the land of Israel when it was laid waste, and over the house of Judah when it went into captivity,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}therefore I am about to give thee to the sons of the East as a pos- session. \uc1\u8216*They shall pitch their tents in thee, and set up in thee their dwell- ings; they shall eat thy fruit, and they shall drink thy milk;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}and I will make Rabbah a pasture for camels, and the cities of the Ammonites a grazing place for flocks, that ye may know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Thus saith Jehovah, "Because thou didst clap thy hands and stamp thy feet, and didst rejoice maliciously over the land of Israel;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}therefore I will stretch out my hand against thee, and make thee the spoil of the nations, and I will cut thee off from the peoples and cause thee to perish out of the lands; I will destroy thee that thou mayest know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Thus saith Jehovah, Because Moab saith: \uc1\u8216*Behold the house of Judah has become like all the nations,\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}therefore behold, I will lay open the flank of Moab, from the cities of its borders to the glory of the land, Beth-jeshimoth, Baal-meon, and Kiriathaim,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and I will give it, together with the Am- monites, to the sons of the East as a possession, that Rabbath-ammon may be no more remembered among the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And on Moab will I execute judgment, that they may know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Thus saith Jehovah, Because Edom hath acted revengefully toward the house of Judah, and hath incurred great guilt by taking bitter revenge,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}therefore thus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8216*I will stretch out my hand against Edom and I will cut off from it man and beast, and make it desolate; from Teman to Dedan they shall fall by the sword.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And I will execute my vengeance upon Edom by the hand of my people Israel and they shall do to Edom according to my anger and my fury, and she shall know my vengeance,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Thus saith Jehovah, Because the Philistines acted revengefully, and took revenge in a spirit of spite to destroy in perpetual hate,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}therefore thus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8216*Behold, I will stretch out my hands against the Philistines, and I will cut off the Cherethites, and destroy the rest of the sea-coast,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and execute great vengeance upon them, that they may know that I am Jehovah, when I execute my vengeance upon them.\uc1\u8217*
