{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi-2440\li2800
 And they shall know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}For thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*Behold, I am about to bring against Tyre Nebuchadnezzar, king of Babylon, the king of kings, from the north with horses and chariots and horsemen and a host of many peoples.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Thy daughters on the mainland he will slay with the sword, and he will build a tower against thee, and raise up a mound against thee, and raise up shields against thee;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and he will direct the shock of his battering rams against thy walls, and hew down thy towers with his axes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Because of the vast number of his horses, their dust shall cover thee; at the sound of horsemen, and wheels, and char- iots thy walls shall shake, when he enters thy gates as one enters the city that is taken by storm.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}With the hoofs of horses he will trample all thy streets, he will slay thy people with the sword and thy strong pillars shall go down to the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}They will despoil thee of thy riches and take thy mer- chandise as booty, break down thy walls, and tear down thy pleasant houses; and thy stones and thy timber and thy dust they will cast in the midst of the waters.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And I will still the sound of thy songs, the music of thy harps shall be heard no more. \uc1\u8220*I will make thee a bare rock; thou shalt be a place in which to spread nets; thou shalt never again be rebuilt, for I, Jehovah, have spoken,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of Jehovah.
\par}

