{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The New Epoch in Ezekiel\uc1\u8217*s Work

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 33}This word of Jehovah came to me,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2} Son of man, speak to the sons of thy people, and say to them, \uc1\u8217*When I bring the sword upon a land, and the people of the land take one of their number and make him their watchman; if, when he sees the sword coming upon the land, he blows the trumpet and warns the people;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}then whoever hears the sound of the trumpet, and does not take warning and the sword come and take him away, his blood shall be upon his own head.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}He heard the sound of the trumpet, and took not warning; his blood shall be upon him; whereas if he had taken warning he would have saved his life.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}But if the watchman, when he sees the sword coming, does not bloiw the trumpet, and the people are not warned, and the sword comes and take one of them; he is taken. away on account of his iniquity, but his blood will I require at the watchman\uc1\u8217*s hand.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}As for thee, son of man, I have set thee as a watchman to the house of Israel; therefore when thou hearest the word at my mouth, give them warning from me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}When I say to the wickedY \uc1\u8220*Thou shalt surely die,\uc1\u8221* and thou dost not speak to warn the wicked from his way; he shall die for his iniquity, but his blood will I require at thy hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Nevertheless, if thou warn the wicked of his way to turn from it, and he turn not from his way; he shall die for his iniquity, but thou hast saved thyself.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}And thou, son of man, say to the house of Israel: \uc1\u8216*Thus ye say: \uc1\u8220*Our transgressions and our sins are upon us, and through them we pine away; how can we live?"\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Say to them, \uc1\u8216*As I live, saith Jehovah, I have no pleasure in the death of the wicked, but that the wicked turn from his way and live. Turn ye, turn ye from your evil ways; for why will ye die, O house of Israel?\uc1\u8221*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And thou, son of man, say to the sons of thy people, \uc1\u8216*The righteousness of the righteous shall not deliver him in the day of his transgression: and as for the wickedness of the wicked, he shall not fall thereby in the day that he turn- eth from his wickedness; neither shall he that is righteous be able to live thereby in the day that he sinneth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}When I say to the righteous, \uc1\u8220*Thou shalt surely live,\uc1\u8221* and he trusts in his righteousness, and commits iniquity, none of his righteous deeds shall be remembered; but for his iniquity that he hath committed, he shall die.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Again, when I say to the wicked, \uc1\u8220*Thou shalt surely die;\uc1\u8221* if he turn from his sin, and do that which is lawful and right,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and restores the pledge, gives again that which he had taken by robbery, and walks in the statutes of life, committing no iniquity; he shall surely live, he shall not die.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}None of his sins that he hath committed shall be remembered against him; he hath done that which is lawful and right; he shall surely live.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Yet the sons of thy people say, \uc1\u8220*The way of the Lord is not right;\uc1\u8221* but it is their way that is not right.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}When the righteous turns from his righteousness, and commits iniquity, he shall even die thereby.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}And when the wicked turns from his wickedness, and does that which is lawful and right, he shall live thereby.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Yet ye say, \uc1\u8220*The way of the Lord is not right.\uc1\u8221* O house of Israel, I will judge each of you according to his acts.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}In the twelfth year of our captivity, in the fifth day of the tenth month, one who had escaped from Jerusalem came to me, saying, The city is smitten.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Now the hand of Jehovah had been upon me in the evening, before the one who had escaped, came; and he had opened my mouth, in expectation of his coming to me in the morning; and my mouth was open and I was no more dumb.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}This word of Jehovah came to me: \uc1\u8220*The inhabitants of the ruins in the land of Israel are saying, \uc1\u8217*Abraham was but one man,\uc1\u176* and he received the whole land as a possession, while we are many, the land is given to us as a possession.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Therefore say to them, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Ye eat with the blood, and worship idols, and commit acts of bloodshed; shall ye possess the land?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Ye depend upon your swords, ye commit abomination and ye defile one another\uc1\u8217*s wives, shall ye possess the land?\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}Thus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8217*As I live, those who are in the ruins shall fall by the sword, and those who are in the open field shall be given to the wild beasts to devour, and those who are in the strongholds and in the caves shall die of the pestilence;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}and I will make the land waste and desolate, and the pride of its might shall cease, and the mountains of Israel shall be desolate, with no one passing through them;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}and they shall know that Iam Jehovah, when I make the land desolate and waste, for all the abominations which they have done.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}As for thee, son of man, the sons of thy people talk about thee beside the walls, and at the doors of their houses, and say! one to another, \uc1\u8220*Come, hear! what is the word that cometh forth from Jehovah?\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}They come in to thee as people come, and sit before thee, and hear thy words, and do them not. Falsehoods are in their mouths, and their hearts are set on their own gain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Behold, thou art to them as a love song, of beautiful tone and excellently played; they hear thy words, but do them not.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}But when it comes to pass \uc1\u8212*behold, it comes! They will know that there was a prophet among them.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Israel\uc1\u8217*s Traitorous Rulers and the Future Restoration

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 34}This word of Jehovah also came to me:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Son of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel, prophesy and say to the shepherds, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: "Woe to the shepherds of Israel who only fed themselves. Should not shepherds feed the flock?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Ye have eaten the milk and clothed yourselves with the wool, ye have killed the fatlings, but my flock ye have not fed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}The weak ye have not strengthened, the sick ye have not healed, the crippled ye have not bound up, ye have not brought back that which was driven away, ye have not sought that which was lost, and the strong ye have ruled harshly.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}So my flock has been scattered because there was no shepherd, and has become food for all the wild beasts of the field.\uc1\u176* My flock hath wandered on all the mountains and on every high hill, and they were scattered? over all the face of the earth with none who searched and sought for them.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore, ye shepherds, hear the word of Jehovah, As I live, is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah, inasmuch as my flock has become the prey and food of all the beasts of the field, because there was no one to shepherd them, for my shepherds cared not for my flock, but the shepherds fed themselves, and my flock they did not feed,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}therefore, O shepherds,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*Behold, I am against the shepherds, and I will require my flock at their hands, and I will cause them to cease from tending my flock; no longer shall the shepherds feed themselves, for I will rescue my flock from their mouths, that it may no longer be food for them.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Por thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*Behold, I myself, will seek for my flock and search them out,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}as a shepherd searches for his flock on the day when his sheep are scattered, so will I search for my flock, and deliver them from ali the places whither they have been scattered in the day of cloud and darkness.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And I will take them from among the peoples, and will gather them from the lands, and bring them into their own habitable land, and feed them on" the mountains of Israel, in the valleys, and in all the habitable parts of the land.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}With good pasture will I feed them, and on the high mountains of Israel shall be their pasture. There they shall lie down in a good habitation, and feed on rich pasturage in the mountains of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I myself will be the shepherd of my flock, and I will lead them to pasture,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8217*The lost I will seek, what is driven away I will bring back, the crippled I will bind up, the sick I will restore to strength, over the fat and the strong I will watch,\uc1\u8221*I will be a righteous shepherd to them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}As for you, my flock,\uc1\u8217* thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*I will judge between the sheep and the rams and the he-goats.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Is it not enough for you to feed on the good pasture, that ye must trample with your feet the rest of the pasture ? And to drink of clear water, that ye must foul the rest with your feet,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}so that my flock must eat what ye have trampled down and drink what ye have fouled with your feet?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Therefore thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216* Behold I myself will judge between the fat sheep and the lean sheep{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}because ye push with side and shoulder, and thrust with your horns, all the feeble sheep, until ye scatter them abroad.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And I will deliver my flock and they shall no longer be a prey, and I will judge between sheep and sheep.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And I will set up over them one shepherd, he shall feed them, namely, my servant, David. And he shall feed them, and he shall be their shepherd.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And I, Jehovah, will be their God, and my servant David shall be prince among them; I, Jehovah, have spoken.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25} And I will make with them a covenant of peace, and will put away wild beasts from the land, so that they may dwell securely in the wilderness, and sleep in the forests.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And I will give them showers of rain in its season, and I will send the dashing rain in its time, rains of blessing shall there be;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}and the trees of the field shall yield their fruit, and the earth shall give its increase, and they shall be secure in their habitable land, and know that I am Jehovah, when I break the frame of their yoke, and deliver them from the hands of those who have made them slaves.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}They shall no longer be afraid of the nations, the beasts of the field shall not devour them, and they shall dwell securely with none to make them afraid.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And I shall provide for them a successful planting, so that they shall no longer be consumed by hunger in the land, and shall never again receive the reproach of the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And they shall know that I, Jehovah, am their God and that they, the house of Israel, are my people,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}\uc1\u8216*My flock are ye, the flock that I tend, and I am your God,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.
\par}

