{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Because thou didst cherish eternal enmity and didst deliver over the Israelites to the sword in the time of their calamity, at the time of their final punishment,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}therefore as I live, is the oracle of Jehovah, thou art guilty of blood, and blood shall pursue thee,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and I will make Mount Seir a waste and desolation, and I will cut off from it those who come and go therefrom,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}and I will fill its mountains with the! slain. On thy hills and thy valleys and all thy watercourses shall fall those slain with the sword;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}and I will make thee n everlasting desolation and thy cities shall not be inhabited, that thou mayest know that I am Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Because thou saidst, the two nations and the two lands shall be mine, and I take possession of them (although Jehovah was there),{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}therefore, as I live, is the oracle of Jehovah, I will deal with thee according to the anger and jealousy wherewith, because of thy hatred, thou didst deal with them, and I will make myself known in thee when I judge thee,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and thou shalt know that I, Jehovah, have heard all thy revilings, which thou utteredst against the mountains of Israel, saying, They are desolate, they are given to us to devour, and thou spokest arrogantly against me! I heard it! \uc1\u8220*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}hus saith Jehovah, \uc1\u8220*\uc1\u8216* As thou didst rejoice over my land, because it was desolate, thus will I deal with thee. Desolate shalt thou be, Mount Seir, and all Edom, all of it, that thou* mayest know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Restoration of the Land of Judah

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 36}And thou son of man, prophesy to the mountains of Israel, and say, Ye mountains of Israel, hear the word of Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: "Because the enemy hath said against you, Aha! and the ancient high places have become our possession,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}therefore prophesy, and say, Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: Inasmuch as they have made you desolate, and crushed you on every side, that ye might become the possession of the rest of the nations, and ye are the popular talk and gossip,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}therefore, O mountains of Israel, hear the word of Jehovah: Thus saith Jehovah to the mountains and to the hills, and to the watercourses and to the valleys, to the desolate wastes and to the deserted cities which have become a prey and a derision to the rest of the nations, which are around about you\uc1\u8212*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}therefore thus saith Jehovah, verily, in the heat of my jealousy have I spoken against the rest of the nations and against all Edom, that have appropriated my land to them- selves as a possession, with heartfelt joy, with malicious spite, in order to take its common pasture land? as prey.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Therefore prophesy concerning the land of Israel, and say to the mountains and to the hills, to the watercourses and to the valleys, Thus saith Jehovah: Behold, I speak in my jealousy and in my wrath, because ye have borne the reproach of the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Therefore thus saith Jehovah: I swear that the nations that are round about you shall surely bear their own shame.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}But ye, O mountains of Israel, ye shall put forth your branches, and yield your fruit to my people Israel; for they will quickly come.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}For, behold, I am with you, and I will turn toward you, and ye shall be tilled and sown;  v 10 and I will make the men upon you many, all the house of Israel, even all of it; and the cities shall be inhabited and the waste places rebuilt;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}and I will make the men and beasts upon you many, and they shall increase and be fruitful; and I will cause you to be inhabited as in your former estate, and I will do better for you than in your beginnings; and ye shall know that I am Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Yea, I will cause men to walk upon you, even my people Israel; and they shall possess thee and thou shalt be their inheritance, and thou shalt no more bereave them of children.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: Because they say to thee, Thou hast devoured men, and bereaved thy nation,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}therefore thou shalt devour men no more, nor bereave thy nation any more, saith the Lord Jehovah. \uc1\u8220*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}I will no longer let the reproach of the nations be heard against? thee, neither shalt thou hear the shame of the peop any more,\uc1\u174* saith the Lord Jehovah."\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Moreover this word of Jehovah came to me,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Son of man, when the house of Israel dwelt in their own land, they defiled it by their ways and by their deeds; their ways before me were as the uncleanness of a woman in her impurity.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Therefore I poured out my wrath upon them for the blood which they had poured out upon the land, and because they had defiled it with their idols.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}I scattered them among the nations and they were dispersed among the countries; according to their ways and deeds I judged them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}But when they! came to the nations, whither they went, they profaned my holy name, in that men said of them, \uc1\u8216*These are the people of Jehovah, and they have come forth out of his land.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}But I had regard for my holy name, which the house of Israel profaned among the nations whither they went.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Therefore say to the house of Israel, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*I act not for your sake, O house of Israel, but for my holy name, which ye have profaned among the nations whither ye have gone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And I will make sacred my great name which hath been profaned among the nations, which ye have profaned in the midst of them; and the nations shall know that I am Jehovah, when through you I shall be sanctified in their sight.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}For I will take you from among the nations, and gather you out of all the countries and will bring you into your own land.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And I will sprinkle clean water upon you, and ye shall be cleansed from all your filthiness, and from all your idols will I cleanse you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}I will also give you a new heart, and a new spirit will I put within you; and I will take away your stony heart, and I will give you a heart of flesh.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And I will put my spirit within you, and cause you to live according to my statutes, nd ye shall keep mine ordinances and do them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And ye shall dwell in the land that I gave to your fathers; and ye shall be my people and I will be your God.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And I will save you from all your uncleannesses; and I will call for the grain, and make it plentiful, and inflict no famine upon you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And I will make plentiful the fruit of the tree, and the increase of the field, that ye may receive no more the reproach of famine among the nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}Then shall ye remember your evil ways, and your deeds that were not good; and ye shall loathe yourselves in your own sight because of your iniquities and your abominations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}Not for your sake do I do this, saith the Lord Jehovah, be it known to you; be ashamed and confounded for your ways, O house of Israel.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*In the day that I cleanse you from all your iniquities, I will cause the cities to be inhabited, and the waste places shall be rebuilt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}And the land that was desolate shall be tilled, instead of being a desolation in the sight of all those who passed by.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}And they shall say, \uc1\u8220*This land that was desolate is become like the Garden of Eden; and the waste places and desolate and ruined cities are fortified and inhabited.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}Then the na- tions that are left round about you shall know that I, Jehovah, have rebuilt the ruined places, and planted that which was desolate; I, Jehovah, have spoken it,and will do it.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 37}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216* This petition also will I grant to the house of Israel, that I may do it for them; I will increase their men like a flock,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}Like the sacrificial flock, like the flock of Jerusa- lem at her festivals, so the waste cities shall be filled with flocks of men; and they shall know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Resurrection of the Nation

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 37}The hand of Jehovah was upon me, and he brought me by the spirit and set me down in the midst of the valley; and it was full of bones.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And he caused me to pass by them round about; and, behold, there were very many on the surface of the valley; and, lo, they were very dry.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And he said to me, Son of man, can these bones live? And I answered, O Lord Jehovah, thou knowest.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Again he said to me, Prophesy over these bones, and say to them, O ye dry bones, hear the word of Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Thus saith Jehovah to these bones: \uc1\u8220*Behold I am about to put breath into you, that ye may live.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And I will put sinews on you, and will clothe you with flesh, and cover you with skin, and put breath in you, that ye may live; and know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}So I prophesied as he commanded me: and as I prophesied, there was an earthquake; and the bones came together, bone to its bone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And I beheld, and, lo, there were sinews upon them, and flesh had clothed them, and skin covered them; but there was no breath in them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then he said to me, Prophesy to the breath, prophesy, son of man, and say to the breath, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: "Come from the four winds, O breath, and breathe upon these slain, that they may live.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}So I prophesied as he commanded me, and the breath came into them, and they lived, and stood upon their feet, an exceedingly great host.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Then he said to me, O man, these bones are the whole house of Israel: behold, they say, \uc1\u8220*Our bones are dried up, and our hope is lost; we are com- pletely ruined.\uc1\u8221*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Therefore prophesy, and say to them, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Behold, I will open your graves, and raise you from your graves, O my people; and I will bring you into the land of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And ye shall know that I am Jehovah ,when I have opened your graves, and raised you from your graves, O my people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And I will put my spirit in you, that ye may live, and I will restore you to your own land: that ye may know that ie Jehov ah, have spoken it and performed it,\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*\uc1\u8212*is the oracle of Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}This word also came to me from Jehovah:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8220*Do thou, O man, take a stick, and write upon it, JUDAH AND THE ISRAELITES ASSOCIATED WITH HIM: then take another stick, and write upon it, JOSEPH, AND ALL THE HOUSE OF ISRAEL ASSOCIATED witH HIM.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then join them together, so that they may become one stick in thy hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And when the children of thy people shall say to thee, \uc1\u8216*Wilt thou not show us what this means?\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}say to them, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Behold, I am about to take the stick of Joseph, which is in the hand of Ephraim, and the tribes of Israel associated with him; and I will unite them with the stick of Judah, and make them one stick, and they shall be united in my hand.\uc1\u8217*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And let the sticks on which thou writest be in thy hand before their eyes.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}And say to them, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: "Behold, I am about to take the Israelites from among the nations, whither they are gone, and gather them from all sides, and bring fem into their own land:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}and I will make them one nation in the land, upon the mountains of Israel; and there shall be one king over them all; and they shall be no longer two nations, neither shall they be divided into two kingdoms any longer;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}nor shall they defile themselves any more with their idols, nor with their detestable things, nor with any of their transgressions; but I will save them from all their apostasies wherein they have Sinead: and will cleanse them: so shall they be my people, and I will be their God.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And my servant David shall be king over them; and they all shall have one shepherd: they shall also walk in mine ordinances, and observe my statutes, and do them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And they shall dwell in the land that I have given to my servant Jacob, wherein their fathers dwelt: and they shall dwell therein, they and their sons, forever: and David my servant shall be their prince forever.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}Moreover I will make a covenant of peace with them; it shall be an everlasting covenant with them; and I will establish them, and multiply them, and set my sanctuary in the midst of them forevermore.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}My dwelling place also shall be with them; and I will be their God, and they shall be my people.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And the nations shall know that I am Jehovah who sanctifieth Israel, when my sanctuary shall be in the midst of them forevermore.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 Jehovah\uc1\u8217*s Ultimate Victory over the Hostile Heathen Powers

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 38}This word of Jehovah also came to me,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Son of man, turn thy face against Gog, prince of Rosh, Meshach, and Tubal, and prophesy against him,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}and say, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Behold, I am against thee, O Gog, prince of Rosh, Meshach, and Tubal,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}and I will turn thee about, and I will put hooks in thy jaws, and I will lead thee forth together with all thine army, horses, and horsemen, clad in complete armor, a mighty host with shield and buckler, all of them armed with swords,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Paras, Cush, and Put with them, all with buckler and helmet,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Gomer and all its hordes, the house of Togarmah, from the extreme north, and all his hordes, many peoples with thee.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Be prepared, yea, hold thyself ready, thou and all thy host assembled with thee, and be a reserve for me,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}after many days thou wilt be mustered forth, after many years thou shalt come against the land that has been restored from desolation, to a people gathered from many nations, against the mountains of Israel which were a continual desolation; but she has been brought out from the nations, and all of them are dwelling in safety.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Thou shalt go up like a storm, like a cloud shalt thou cover the land,\uc1\u8221* thou and all thy host, and the many peoples with thee.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: "On that day plans will come into thy mind and thou wilt form an evil design,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11} and say, I will go up into a land of villages, I will go to those who are friendly, who dwell in security, all of them, dwelling without walls, and having no bars or gates\uc1\u8212*{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}to take spoil, to carry off prey, to turn thy hand against the wastes that have been repeopled, against the people gathered from the nations, having acquired possessions and prop- erty, dwelling at the centre of the earth.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Sheba and Dedan and their mer- chants, Tarsish and all her traders will say to thee, Art thou come to get spoil? Hast thou gathered thy host to carry off spoil, to take silver and gold, to seize possessions and property, to gather much plunder?\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Therefore prophesy, O son of man, and say to Gog, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Wilt thou not at that time, when my people Israel are dwelling in security, bestir thy self,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and come from thy place, from the extreme north, thou and many peoples with thee, all riding on horses, a mighty host, a vast army?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And wilt thou not come up after many days against my people Israel like a cloud to cover the land? Yea, I will bring thee up against my land, that the nations may know what I am, when through thee I show myself to be holy in their sight.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*Art thou not he of whom I declared in former days, through my servants, the prophets of Israel, who in those days prophesied through the years that I would bring thee against them?{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And on that day, the day when Gog cometh against the land of Israel,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah, \uc1\u8216*then will my fury be thoroughly aroused,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}yea, in my jealousy, the heat of my wrath I declare: Verily on that day there shall be a great earthquake upon the land of Israel;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}all the fishes of the sea and the birds of the heavens, and the beasts of the fields, and all creeping things that creep upon the earth, and all men, who are on the face of the earth, shall tremble at my presence. And the mountains shall be torn apart and the cliffs shall topple over, and every wall shall fall to the ground.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}And I will summon every terror against him,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of Jehovah; \uc1\u8216*every man\uc1\u8217*s sword shall be against his brother!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And with pestilence and with blood will I enter into judgment against him; and I will rain upon him and upon his hordes and upon the many peoples that are with him, an overflowing flood, and hailstones, fire, and brimstone.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And I will show my greatness and sanctity in the eyes of many nations, and they shall know that I am Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 39}And thou, Son of man, prophesy against Gog, and say, \uc1\u8217*Thus saith Jehovah: "Behold, I am against thee, O Gog, prince of Rosh, Meshach and Tubal;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}and I will turn thee about and lead thee forth, and will cause thee to come up from the extreme north, and I will bring thee against the mountains of Israel;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And I will smite thy bow from thy left hand, and will cause the arrows to fall from thy right hand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Thou shalt fall upon the mountains of Israel\uc1\u8212*thou, and all thy hordes, and the peoples that are with thee. I will give thee to the ravenous birds of every sort, and to the beasts of the field to be devoured.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Thou shalt fall upon the open field; for I have spoken it,\uc1\u8221* saith Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And I will send a fire on Gog,! and on those who dwell securely in the coast-lands; and they shall know that I am Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And my holy name will I make known in the midst of my people Israel; neither will I suffer my holy name to be profaned any more; and the nations shall know that I, Jehovah, am holy in Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Behold, it cometh, and it shall be done,\uc1\u8221* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah; \uc1\u8220*this is the day of which I have spoken.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}And they who dwell in the cities of Israel shall go forth, and shall make fires of the weapons, and burn them, both the bucklers and the shields, the bows and arrows, the pikes and spears, and they shall use them as firewood seven years,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}so that they shall take no wood out of the forests; for they shall use the weapons as firewood; and they shall plunder those who plundered them, and prey upon those who preyed upon them, is the oracle of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And in that day I will give to Gog a renowned place as a grave in Israel, the valley of Abarim! on the east of the sea; and there shall they bury Gog and his multitude; and they shall call it the valley of Hamon-Gog.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And seven months shall the house of Israel be burying them, that they may cleanse the land.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Yea, all the people of the land shall bury them; and it shall bring to them renown in the day when I show forth my glory,\uc1\u8221* is the oracle of Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And they shall set apart men who shall be continually employed in passing through the land, and in bringing those who remain on the face of the land in order to cleanse it,\uc1\u8221* is the oracle of Jehovah. "After the end of seven months they shall search.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And they who pass through the land shall pass through, and when anyone sees a man\uc1\u8217*s bone, he shall set up a sign by it until the buriers bury it in the valley of Hamon-Gog.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And Hamonah shall also be the name of a city. Thus they shall cleanse the land.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And thou, son of man, speak to birds of every sort and to every beast of the field, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith Jehovah: \uc1\u8220*Assemble, and come; gather from every side to my sacrifice, that I am about to sacrifice for you, even a great sacrifice upon the mountains of Israel, that ye may eat flesh and drink blood.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Ye shall eat the flesh of the mighty and drink the blood of the princes of the earth, of rams, of lambs, of goats, and of bullocks, all of them fatlings of Bashan.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}And ye shall eat fat till ye be full and drink blood till ye be aetneen of my sacrificial feast which I have prepared for you.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And ye shall be filled at my table with horses and riders, with mighty men and all men of war,\uc1\u8221* is the oracle of Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}\uc1\u8220*\uc1\u8217*Thus I will establish my glory among the nations; and all the nations shall see the judgment which I execute, and the hand which I lay upon them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}So the house of Israel shall know that I am their God, from that day and for- ward.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And the nations shall know that the house of Israel went into captivity for their iniquity, because they trespassed against me, and I hid my face from them; so I gave them into the hands of their adversaries and they all fell by the sword;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}according to their uncleanness, and according to their transgres- sions I punished them, and hid my face from them.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Therefore thus saith the Lord Jehovah; \uc1\u8216*Now I will bring back the cap- tivity of Jacob, and have mercy upon the whole house of Israel; and I will be jealous for my holy name.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And they shall forget their shame and all their infidelity which they showed toward me, when they dwell securely in their land, with none to make them afraid,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}when I bring them back from the peoples, and gather them out of the lands of their enemies, and through them show my sanctity in the sight of many nations.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And they shall know that I am Jehovah their God, in that I caused them to go into captivity among the na- tions, and have gathered them to their own land; and I will leave none of them any more there;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}neither will I hide my face any longer from them; for I have poured out my spirit upon the house of Israel,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sb360\sa360\fs32 The Temple Plan

\par}

{\pard
\par}
{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 40}In the twenty-fifth year of our captivity, in the beginning of the year, in the tenth day of the month, in the fourteenth year after the city was taken, on that very day, the hand of Jehovah was laid upon me, and he brought me{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}in an inspired vision to the land of Israel, and set me down upon a very high mountain, on which was a city-like building toward the south.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Thither he brought me, and there was a man whose appearance was like the appearance of bronze, with a flaxen Hue and a measuring reed in his hand; and he was standing in the gateway.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And the man said to me, Son of man, behold with thine eyes, and hear with thine ears, and give heed to all that I shall show thee; for, in order that thou shouldst be shown it wert thou brought hither; declare all that thou seest to the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}There was a wall encircling a temple, and in the man\uc1\u8217*s hand a measuring reed six cubits long, each cubit being equal to a cubit and a handbreadth, and he measured the thickness of the building, one reed; and the height one reed.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then he came to the east gateway and went up its steps and measured East the threshold of the gate one reed wide.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And each guard-room was one  reed long, and one reed broad; and between the guard-rooms were spaces  of five cubits; and the threshold of the gate at the vestibule of the gate on the inner side was one reed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Then he measured the vestibule of the gate, eight cubits, and its jambs, two cubits; and the vestibule of the gate was on the inner side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10} the guard-rooms of the east gate were three on each side; all three were of the same dimensions; and the posts were on both sides.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And he measured the breadth of the entrance to the gateway, ten cubits; and the width of the gate, thirteen cubits;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}and there was a sill one cubit wide, before the guard-rooms on each side; and the guard-rooms, six cubits on both sides.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And he measured the gate from the outer wall of the one guard-room to the the outer wall of the other, twenty -five cubits wide; door opposite door.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}He also measured the vestibule, twenty cubits; and the court reached to the jambs, round about the gateway.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And from the front of the gateway at the entrance to the front of the inner vestibule of the gate were fifty cubits.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And the guard-rooms and their jambs had windows, within the gate round about, and likewise the vestibule had windows round about within; and on each jamb were palm-trees.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}Then he brought me into the outer court, and there were chambers and a pavement made round about the court; thirty chambers were upon the pavement.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}And the pavement was on the side of the gateways; it corresponded to the length of the gateways, that is, the lower pavement.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Then he measured the breadth from the front of the lower gate to the front of the inner court without, one hundred cubits on the east and on the north.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And the north gateway of the outer court, he measured its length and  breadth,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}And there were three guard-rooms on each side; and its jambs and its vestibules corresponded to the measurement of the first gate; its length was fifty cubits, and its breadth twenty cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And its windows and its vestibules and its palm trees measured the same as those of the east gate; and seven steps led up to it; its vestibule was within.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And there was a gate to the inner court opposite the north gate, corresponding to the one on the east; and he measured from gate to gate one hundred cubits.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And he led me toward the south; and he measured its guard-rooms and its jambs and its vestibule; they were of the same dimensions as the  others.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And there were windows in it and in its vestibule round about corresponding to the other windows; the length was fifty cubits, and the breadth twenty-five cubits,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And seven steps led up to it, and its vestibule was within; and it had palm-trees, one on each side of its jambs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And there was a gate to the inner court on the south; and he measured from gate to gate toward the south a hundred cubits.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}Then he brought me to the inner court at the south gateway; and he measured the south gateway; it measured the same as the others;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}its guard-rooms, and posts and vestibule were of the same dimensions as way the preceding; and there were windows in it and in its vestibule round about; it was fifty cubits long and twenty-five cubits wide.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}And its vestibule faced the outer court; and there were palm-trees beside its posts; and the ascent to it had eight steps.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 32}And he brought me to the east side of the inner court; and he measured the gateway; it measured the same as the others;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 33}and its guard-rooms and  posts and vestibules were of the same dimensions as the preceding; and there were windows in it and in the vestibule round about; it was fifty cubits long and twenty-five cubits wide.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 34}And its vestibule faced the outer court; and there were beside its palm-trees posts, one on each side; and the ascent to it had eight steps.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 35}Then he brought me to the north gateway; and he measured the gateway; it measured the same as the others.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 36}And its guard-rooms and posts and  vestibules were of the same dimensions as the preceding; and there were windows in it and in the vestibule round about; it was fifty cubits long and twenty-five cubits wide,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And its vestibule faced the outer court; and there were beside its palm-trees posts, one on each side; and the ascent to it had eight steps.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 38}And there was a chamber with its opening into the vestibule of the gateway; there they washed the burnt-offering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}And in the vestibule of the gateway were two tables on each side, on which were slain the burnt-offerings and the sin-offerings and the guilt-offerings.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 40}And outside the entrance to the gateway on the north, were two tables.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 41}There were four within and four without the gateway; eight tables, upon which the burnt-offerings were slain.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 42}There were also four tables for the burnt-offering, of hewn stone, each a cubit and a half long, and a cubit and a half broad, and a cubit high; on which they laid the instruments wherewith the burnt-offerings and the sacrificial animals were slain,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 43}and projections, one handbreadth in length, were fastened within round about. And over the tables were protecting roofs to keep off the rain and the hot sun.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 44}He brought me outside the gate and into the inner court, and there were two chambers on the inner court, one by the north gate, facing the south, the other by the south gate facing the north.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 45}And he said to me, This chamber, which faces the south, is for the priests, who have charge of the temple;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 46}and the chamber which faces the north is for the priests who have charge of the altar; they are the sons of Zadok, those of the sons of Levi who may come near to Jehovah to serve him.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 47}And he measured the court, a hundred cubits wide, and a hundred cubits broad\uc1\u8212*a perfect square. The altar was in front of the temple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 48}Then he brought me to the porch of the temple, and meas- ured the jambs of the porch on each side, five cubits in thickness, and the width of the gate was fourteen cubits and the pillars of the gate were three cubits thick on each side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 49}The dimensions of the porch were twenty by twelve cubits; and the ascent was by ten steps; and there were pillars by the jambs on each side.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 41}Then he brought me to the hall of the temple and measured the jambs, six cubits broad on each side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And the breadth of the entrance was ten cubits; and the sides of the entrance were five cubits on each side; and he measured its length, forty cubits, and its width, twenty cubits.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Then went into the inner room and measured the jambs of its entrance, two cubits; and the entrance, six cubits; and the side-walls of the entrance, seven cubits on each side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And he measured its length, twenty cubits, and its breadth, twenty cubits, before the hall of the temple. And he said to me, This is the most holy place.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And the hall of the temple, and the inner room and its porch were paneled,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}and the windows latticed and covered. And the galleries round about on their three stories, opposite the threshold, were ceiled with wood round about, from the ground up to the windows,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}and from the door to the inner room and without. And on all the wall round about within and without were drawings{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}and carved cherubim and palm-trees, there being a palm-tree between every two cherubim.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}And each cherub had two faces; the face of a man turned toward the palm-tree on the one side, and the face of a young lion turned toward the palm-tree on the other side; they were carved on all the temple round about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}From the ground to the top of the door were carved cherubim and palm-trees. The wall of the hall of the temple had{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}pilasters. And before the holy place was something that looked like{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}an altar of wood, three cubits high, and two cubits in thickness and two cubits in width; and its corners, and its base and walls were of wood. And he said to me, This is the table that stands before Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And the base of the temple and the holy place had two doors.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And each door had turning leaves; two for each door.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Cherubim and palm-trees were carved on them, as on the walls; and there was a threshold in front of the porch without.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And there were closed windows and palm-trees on both sides of the porch; thus were the side-chambers of the temple and the thresholds.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 41}Then he measured the thickness of the wall of the temple, six cubits; and the width of the side-chambers, four cubits, round about the temple on every side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And the side-chambers were in three stories, one above another, and thirty in each story; and there were abatements all around the walls of the temple that the side-chambers might be fastened to them and not in the walls of the temple.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And the side-chambers became wider as they went up higher and higher, for the temple grew narrower higher and higher up round about the temple; and there was an ascent from the lowest story to the highest by the middle story.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And I also saw that the temple had a raised platform round about; the foundations of the side- chambers were a full reed in height, that is, six great cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}The thickness of the outer wall of the side-chambers, was five cubits; and the space left between the side-chambers that belonged to the temple{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}and the outer chambers was twenty cubits wide round about the temple on each side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And the doors of the side-chambers were toward the open space, one door toward the north and another door toward the south; and the width of the open space of the platform was five cubits round about.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And the building that faced the enclosure on the west was seventy cubits wide; and the wall of the building was five cubits thick round about, and its length ninety cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}So he measured the temple, a hundred cubits long; and the enclosure, and the building, with its walls, a hundred cubits long;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}also the width of the front of the temple, with the eastern enclosure was one hundred cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And he measured the length of the building in front of the rear enclosure, its galleries on both sides, one hundred cubits.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 42}Then he brought me forth into the outer court on the north; and he brought me to the chamber which faced the enclosure and the building on the north.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}One hundred cubits was its length on the north side,\uc1\u8217* and the width was fifty cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}Opposite the space of twenty cubits which belonged to the inner court, and the raised platform which belonged to the outer court, was a gallery on each side in three tiers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And in front of the chambers was a passage-way to the inner court, ten cubits wide and one hundred! cubits long; and their doors were on the north.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}The upper chambers were smaller, for the galleries took away from these, more than from the lower and the middle chambers in the building;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}that is, they were in three stories, and had no pillars like the pillars of the outer courts; therefore the upper was smaller than the lowest and middle chambers.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And the outer wall by the side of the chambers along the outer court in front of the chambers was fifty cubits long;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}that is, the length of the chambers in the outer court was fifty cubits, while in front of it was one hundred cubits.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Below these chambers was the entry on the east side, as one approached them from the outer court;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}at the beginning of the outer wall on the south, in front of the enclosure and the a eenet were chambers,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}with the passage-way before them; they were similar to the chambers on the north; of the same length and width, the same exits and arrangements, and with their doors on the south.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}There was a door at the beginning of the passage-way, directly in front of the wall on the east, as one approached them.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Then said he to me, the north and south chambers are the sacred chambers, where the priests who approach Jehovah shall eat the most holy things; there they shall deposit the most holy things, the cereal-offering, and the sin-offering, and the guilt-offering, for the place is holy.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15} Having finished the measurement of the inner temple he brought me by way of the east gate, and measured it round about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}He measured on the east side five hundred cubits, with the measuring reed round about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}He measured on the north side five hundred cubits by the measuring reed round about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}He measured on the south side five hundred cubits by the measuring reed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Then he turned to the west side and meas- ured five hundred cubits by the measuring reed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}He measured it on the four sides; and it had a wall round about, five hundred cubits in length and five hundred cubits in width, to separate between the sacred and the common.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 43}Then he brought me to the east gate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And behold the glory of the God of Israel came from the east; and his voice was like the sound of many waters; and the earth shone with his glory.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And the vision which I saw was like that which I saw when he came to destroy the city; and the visions were like that which I saw by the River Chebar; and I fell on my face.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then the glory of Jehovah came into the temple by the east gate.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And the Spirit took me up, and brought me into the inner court; and, behold, the glory of Jehovah filled the temple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Then I heard one speaking to me from the temple, as One stood by me.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And he said to me, O man, this is the place of my throne, and the place for the soles of my feet, where I will dwell in the midst of the Israelites forever. And the house of Israel, they and their kings, shall no more defile my holy nameY with their idolatry and with the corpses of their kings{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}by placing their thresholds by my threshold, and their door-posts beside my door-post, with only a wall between me and them, thus defiling my holy name by the abominations which they have committed; therefore I have destroyed them in mine anger.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Now let them put away their idolatry, and the corpses of their kings, far from me, that I may dwell in the midst of them forever.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Do thou, O man, show the house of Israel the temple, its appearance and its pattern,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}that they may be ashamed of all that they have done, describe to them the temple and its construction, its exits and its entrances and its form, and make known to them all its ordinances and laws; and write it down in their sight, that they may take heed to perform all its forms and ordinances.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}This is the law of the temple: on the top of the mountain its whole territory shall be sacred. Behold, this is the law of the temple.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And these are the measurements of the altar in cubits of a cubit and a handbreadth: the base shall be a cubit high, one cubit wide, with a border around its edge about a span wide; and this shall be the height of the altar:{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}from the foundation base to the lower ledge shall be two cubits, and the width one cubit; and from the smaller ledge to the greater ledge shall be four cubits, and the width one cubit.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And the alter hearth shall be four cubits high; and above the hearth shall be four horns, one cubit high.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}And the altar hearth shall be twelve cubits square.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And the ledge shall be fourteen cubits square; and the border about it shall be half a cubit; and the base one cubit wide round about. Its steps shall face the east.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Then he said to me, O man, thus saith the Lord Jehovah: \uc1\u8216*These are the regulations for the altar in the day when it is completed, \uc1\u8220*In order that burnt-offerings may be offered and blood sprinkled on it,{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}thou shalt give to the priests the Levites who are of the family of Zadok, who approach to serve me,\uc1\u8221* saith the Lord Jehovah, \uc1\u8220*a young bullock as a sin-offering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And they shall take some of its blood, and put it on the four horns, and on the four corners of the ledge, and on the border round about; thus shall they cleanse it and make atonement for it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}They shall also take the bullock of the sin-offering, and it shall be burnt in the appointed place outside the temple.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}And on the second day they shall offer a male goat without blemish as a sin-offering, and shall cleanse the altar, as they cleansed it with the bullock.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}\uc1\u176*When they have made an end of cleansing it, they shall offer a young bullock and a ram from the flock without blemish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And they shall present them before Jehovah, and the priests shall sprinkle salt upon them and they shall offer them as a burnt-offering to Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}Seven days shalt thou provide daily a goat as a sin-offering;) they shall also provide a young bullock, and a ram from the flock, without blemish.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}For seven days shall they make atonement for the altar and purify and consecrate it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}At the end of these days, on the eighth day and thereafter, the priests shall present your burnt-offerings and your peace-offerings upon the altar; and I will accept you,\uc1\u8221* saith the Lord Jehovah.\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 44}Then he took me back to the outer eastern gate of the sanct- uary, and it was closed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Then he said to me, This gate shall remain closed; it shall not be opened, and none shall enter by it; for Jehovah the God of Israel hath entered by it, therefore it shall remain closed.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}As for the prince he may sit therein? to eat bread in the presence of Jehovah; he shall enter by the vestibule of the gate, and by the same way shall he go out.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Then he took me by way of the north gate to the front of the temple; and I looked and behold, the glory of Jehovah filled the temple. And I fell on my face.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And Jehovah said to me, O man, give heed, see with thine eyes and hear with thine ears all that I tell thee regarding the regulations of the temple of Jehovah and all its laws, and observe carefully how to enter the temple by all of the exits of the sanctuary.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}Say to the rebellious, even to the house of Israel, \uc1\u8216*Thus saith the Lord Jehovah, "Enough of all your abominations, O house of Israel, \uc1\u8220*in that ye have brought foreigners, neither consecrated in heart nor flesh, to be in my sanctuary to profane it,\uc1\u176*when ye offered me bread, fat and blood; thus ye have broken my covenant, with all your abominations!{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And ye have not taken charge of my holy things but ye have set them as keepers in charge of my sanctuary.\uc1\u8221*\uc1\u8217*
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Therefore thus saith the Lord Jehovah, \uc1\u8217*No foreigner, consecrated neither in heart nor flesh, of all the foreigners who are among the Israelites, shall enter my sanctuary.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}But those Levites who went far from me, when Is- rael went astray, who went astray from me after their idols, shall bear their guilt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}Yet they shall be ministers in my sanctuary, having oversight at the gates of the temple, and ministering in the temple, they shall slay the burnt-offering and the sacrifice for the people, and they shall stand before them and minister to them.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}Since they were wont to minister to them before their idols, and were a stumbling-block of iniquity to the house of Israel; therefore I have taken a solemn oath against them,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah, \uc1\u8216*and they shall bear their guilt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And they shall not approach me to act as priests to me, so as to come near any of my sacred things, or to those which are most sacred; but they shall bear their shame and the punishment for the abominations which they have committed;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Iwill make them responsible for the care of the temple, for all its service, and for all that shall be done therein.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}But the priests the Levites, the sons of Zadok, who took charge of my sanctuary when the Israelites went astray from me, shall come near to me to minister to me, and they shall stand before me to offer to me fat and blood,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}\uc1\u8216*They shall enter my sanctuary, and they shall approach near to my table to minister to me, and they shall keep my charge.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}When they enter the gates of the inner court, they shall wear linen garments, but they shall have on no wool while they are officiating in the gates of the inner court and in the temple.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}They shall have linen turbans upon their heads and linen breeches on their loins; they shall not gird themselves with anything that causeth sweat.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}But when they go forth to the outer court to the people, they shall put off the garments in which they were officiating, and lay them in the sacred chambers; and they shall put on other garments, that they may not sanctify the people with their garments.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}Neither shall they shave their heads, nor suffer their hair to grow long; they shall cut off their hair.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}None of the priests shall drink wine, when they enter the inner court.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Neither shall they marry a widow nor a divorced woman, but only Israelitish virgins or the widow of a priest.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And they shall teach my people the difference between the sacred and the common, and instruct them how to discern between the unclean and the clean.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And in a controversy they shall act as judges, judging it acording to my ordinances. And they shall keep my laws and my statutes and in all my appointed feasts; and they shall maintain the sanctity of my sabbaths.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}And they shall not approach a dead person to defile themselves; except in the case of a father, or a mother, or a son, or a daughter, or brother, or unmarried sister.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 26}And after his defilement, a priest shall be given seven days.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 27}And on the day that he goeth into the inner court, to minister in the sanctuary, he shall offer his sin-offering,\uc1\u8217* is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 28}And they shall have not inheritance; I am their inheritance; and ye shall give them no possession in Israel; I am their possession.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 29}They shall eat the cereal-offering, and the sin-offering, and the guilt-offering; and every devoted thing in Israel shall be theirs.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 30}And the best of all the firstfruits of every thing, and every contribution of every thing, of all your contribu- tions, shall belong to the priest; ye shall also give to the priests the best of your dough, that a blessing may rest on thy household.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 31}The priests shall not eat of any thing that dieth a natural death or hath been mangled, whether it be bird or beast.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 45}When ye allot the land as inheritance, ye shall offer as a special gift\uc1\u174* to Jehovah, a sacred portion of the land, five thousand cubits long, and twenty thousand cubits wide; it shall be sacred throughout its entire extent.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And out of this area shalt thou measure off a space twenty- five thousand cubits long and ten thousand cubits wide, and on it shall the sanctuary, the most holy stand.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}It is a holy portion of the land; it shall belong to the priests who are the ministers in the sanctuary, who draw near to minister to Jehovah; and it shall be a place for their houses, and an open space for the sanctuary. Out of this a square of five hundred cubits shall be for the sanctuary, with an open space fifty cubits wide around it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}And a space twenty-five thousand cubits long and ten thousand wide shall belong to the Levites, the ministers of the temple; their possession shall it be for cities in which to dwell.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And as the possession of the city, ye shall assign a space five thousand cubits wide, and twenty-five thousand long, bende the sacred reservation; it shall belong to the whole house of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}And the prince shall have the space on both sides of the sacred reservation and the possession of the city, facing the sacred reservation and the possession of the city, on the west and on the east, and of the same length as one of the portions of the tribes, from the west border to the the east border{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}of the land. It shall be his possession in Israel; and the princes of Israel shall no more oppress my people, but shall give the land to the house of Israel according to their tribes.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah, Enough, O princes of Israel ! Put away violence and oppression, and  practice justice and righteousness! Free my people from your robberies, is the oracle of the Lord Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Ye shall have just balances, and a just ephah, and a just bath.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}The ephahY and the bath shall be of one measure; the bath shall contain the tenth part of a homer, and the ephah the tenth part of a homer; the homer shall be the standard of measurement.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And the shekel shall be twenty gerahs; five shekels shall be valued as five shekels, and ten as ten, and your maneh shall be fifty shekels.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}This is the contribution that ye shall offer: the sixth part of an ephah out of every homer of wheat; and ye shall give the sixth part of an ephah out of every homer of barley;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}and the fixed proportion of oil, shall be the tenth part of a bath out of every cor, the cor being ten baths;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}and one lamb out of a flock of two hundred, from all the families of Israel, as a cereal-offering, and a burnt-offering, and peace-offerings, to make atone- ment for them, saith the Lord Jehovah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}All the people of the land shall contribute to this special gift for the prince in Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}And it shall be the prince\uc1\u8217*s part to give the burnt-offerings, and the cereal-offerings, and the libations at the feasts, and on the new moons, and on the sabbaths, at all the feast days of the house of Israel: he shall prepare the sin-offering, and the cereal-offering, and the burnt-offering, and the peace-offerings, to make atonement for the house of Israel.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Tn the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month, ye shall observe the feast of the passover; seven days unleavened bread shall be eaten.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}On that day the prince shall provide for himself and for all the people of the land a bullock as a sin-offering;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}and during the seven days of the feast he shall provide a burnt-offering for Jehovah, seven bullocks and seven rams without blemish; and a male goat daily as a sin-offering.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}And he shall provide a cereal-offering, an ephah to a bullock, and an ephah to a ram, and of oil a hin to an ephah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 25}In the seventh month, on the fifteenth day of the month, at the feast, shall he do the same during the seven days, for the sin-offering, the burnt-offering, the cereal-offering, and for the oil.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 46}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah, The east gate of the inner court shall be shut during the six working days; but on the sabbath day, and on the day of the new moon it shall be open.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}And the prince shall enter from without by the vestibule of the gate, and shall stand by the door-post of the gate; and the priests shall prepare his burnt-offering and his peace-offerings, and he shall worship at the threshold of the gate, ana then go out; but the gate shall not be shut until evening.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}And the people of the fined shall worship at the door of that gate before Jehovah on the sabbaths and on the new moons.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}And the burnt-offering which the prince shall offer to Jehovah on the sabbath day shall be six lambs without blemish and one ram without blemish; \uc1\u174*the cereal-offering being an ephah to a ram, and for the lambs as he is able to give, and of oil a hin to an ephah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And on the day of the new moon it shall be a young bullock without blemish and six lambs, and a ram, without blemish;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}and he shall prepare a cereal-offering, an ephah for the bullock, and an ephah for the ram, and for the lambs as he is able, and of oil a hin to an ephah.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}And when the prince shall enter, he shall go in by the vestibule of the gate, and he shall go forth by the same way.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}But when the people of the land shall come before Jehovah in the feast days, he who enters by the north gate to worship shall go out by the south gate; and he who enters by the south gate shall go out by the north gate; none shall return by the gate at which ie came in, but shall go out straight ahead.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}The prince shall go in with them, when they go in, and go out, when they go forth.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}And on the feast days and the festivals the cereal-offering shall be an ephah to a bullock, and an ephah to a ram, and for the lambs as he is able to give, and of oil a hin to an ephah.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And when the prince shall prepare a voluntary-offering, a burnt-offering or peace-offerings as a voluntary-offering to Jehovah, the east gate shall be opened for him, and he shall present he burnt-offering and his peace-offerings, as he doth on the sabbath day; then he shall go out; and after he has gone out the gate shall be shut.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}And he shall provide daily a lamb a year old without blemish as a burnt-offering to Jehovah;! each morning shall he provide it.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}And he shall provide as a cereal-offering with it each morning the sixth part of an ephah, and the third part of a hin of oil, to moisten the fine meal, as a cereal-offering to Jehovah by a perpetual ordinance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}Thus shall he provide the lamb, and the cereal-offering, and the oil, each morning, as a regular burnt-offering.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah, If the prince make a gift to any of his sons, out of his inheritance, it shall belong to his sons; it is their possession by inheritance.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}But if he make a gift out of his inheritance to one of his servants, it shall be his to the year of release; then it shall revert to the prince; but as for his inheritance, it shall belong to his sons.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}Moreover the prince shall not take of the people\uc1\u8217*s inheritance so as to deprive them by force of their possession; he shall give an inheritance to his sons out of his own possession, that none of my people be scattered from his possession.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}Then he brought me through the entry, which was at the side of the gate, into the priests\uc1\u8217* sacred chamber on the north; and there was a place on the extreme western side.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}And he said to me, This is the place where the priests shall boil the guilt-offering and the sin-offering, and bake the cereal-offering, so as not to bring them out into the outer court, thereby making the people sacred.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Then he brought me into the outer court, and made me pass by the four corners of the court; and there in each corner of the court was a court.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}In the four corners of the court there were small\uc1\u176* courts forty cubits long and thirty cubits wide; these four in the corners were of the same size.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And there was a row of stones round about each of the four, and places for boiling were constructed beneath the row of stones round about.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 24}Then he said to me, These are the houses where the ministers of the temple shall boil the sacrifice of the people.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\cf1\f1\fs22 47} Then he brought me to the door of the temple and there was water issuing from under the threshold of the temple eastward\uc1\u8212*the temple faced the east\uc1\u8212*and the water came down on the south side of the temple, to the south side of the altar.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 2}Then he brought me out by the way of the north gate, and led me around outside to the eastern outer gate; and there water was flowing on the south side.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 3}As the man went forth eastward with the line in his hand, he measured a thousand cubits, and he caused me to pass through waters, ankle-deep.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 4}Again he measured a thousand cubits, and caused me to pass through waters, knee-deep. Again he measured a thousand cubits, and caused me to pass through waters, hip-deep.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 5}Afterward he measured a thousand cub- its; and it was a river through which I could not pass, for the waters were deep enough to swim in, a river that could not be forded.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 6}And he said to me, Seest thou, O man? Then he brought me back to the bank of the river.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 7}Now when I had returned, there on the bank of the river were very many trees on both sides.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 8}Then he said to me, These waters issue forth toward the eastern region, and shall descend to the Arabah; and they shall go to the Dead Sea into the salt waters; which waters shall be made fresh.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 9}Every living creature which swarmeth, in every place whither the river cometh, shall live; and the fish shall be very many.t{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 10}Fishers shall stand by it from Engedi even to En-eglaim; it shall be a place for the spreading of nets; its fish shall be like the fish of the Great Sea, exceeding many.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 11}But its marshes and pools shall not be made fresh; they shall be left for salt.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 12}And by the bank of the river on both sides shall grow every kind of tree which furnisheth food; their leaves shall not wither, neither shall their fruit fail; every month they shall bear fresh fruit, for their waters issue from the sanctuary, and their fruit shall be for food and their leaves for healing.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 13}Thus saith the Lord Jehovah, This is the border, whereby ye shall allot the land according to the twelve tribes of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 14}Ye shall share it equally, for I swore to give it to your fathers, and this land shall fall to you as your inheritance.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 15}And this is the border of the land on the north: From the Great Sea\uc1\u165* by* Hethlon, to the entrance of{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 16}Hamath, as far as Zedad, Berothah, and Sibraim, which is between the border of Damascus and Hamath; and to Hazerenon, which is on the border of Hauran;{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 17}thus the border shall run from the sea to Hazarenon, so that the territory of Damascus is on the north on the border of Hamath. This is the northern border.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 18}On the east: Between Hauran, Damascus and Gilead and the land of Israel, shall be the Jordan; from the northern border to the eastern sea shall ye measure. This is the eastern border.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 19}On the south: From Tamar as far as the waters of Meriboth-kadesh, to the brook of Egypt, and to the Great Sea. This is the southern border. 
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 20}On the west: The Great Sea from the southern border to a point opposite the entrance of Hamath. This is the western border.
\par}

{\pard\sl280\slmult1\fs24\fi360 
{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 21}Thus ye shall divide this land among yourselves according to the tribe of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 22}Ye shall allot it as an inheritance for yourselves and the aliens residing among you, who have begotten children among you; and they shall be reckoned with you as the native-born among the Israelites; they shall be assigned a portion with you among the tribes of Israel.{\super\f1\cf2\fs24 23}And ye shall give the alien his portion in the land in which he dwells, saith the Lord Jehovah.
\par}

